abstract: Senior lawmakers announced a tentative agreement Thursday on an almost $1.4 trillion government-wide spending bill that would stave off a federal shutdown next weekend and split the differences on a number of contentious issues.
snippet: Senior lawmakers announced a tentative agreement Thursday on an almost $1.4 trillion government-wide spending bill that would stave off a federal shutdown next weekend and split the differences on a number of contentious issues.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Senior lawmakers announced a tentative agreement Thursday on an almost $1.4 trillion government-wide spending bill that would stave off a federal shutdown next weekend and split the differences on a number of contentious issues.
headline_main: Tentative Deal Would Avert Possible Looming Federal Shutdown
headline_print_headline: Tentative Deal Would Avert Possible Looming Federal Shutdown

abstract: The Pentagon on Thursday flight-tested a missile that had been banned under a treaty that the United States and Russia abandoned last summer. Some U.S. arms control advocates said the test risks an unnecessary arms race with Moscow.
snippet: The Pentagon on Thursday flight-tested a missile that had been banned under a treaty that the United States and Russia abandoned last summer. Some U.S. arms control advocates said the test risks an unnecessary arms race with Moscow.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Pentagon on Thursday flight-tested a missile that had been banned under a treaty that the United States and Russia abandoned last summer. Some U.S. arms control advocates said the test risks an unnecessary arms race with Moscow.
headline_main: Pentagon Tests Long-Banned Ballistic Missile Over Pacific
headline_print_headline: Pentagon Tests Long-Banned Ballistic Missile Over Pacific

abstract: Cory Booker will remain in the Democratic presidential race even though he does not expect to qualify for next week's primary debate, he announced Thursday, after a burst of fundraising support has given him the resources he needs to continue his bid.
snippet: Cory Booker will remain in the Democratic presidential race even though he does not expect to qualify for next week's primary debate, he announced Thursday, after a burst of fundraising support has given him the resources he needs to continue his ...
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Cory Booker will remain in the Democratic presidential race even though he does not expect to qualify for next week's primary debate, he announced Thursday, after a burst of fundraising support has given him the resources he needs to continue his bid.
headline_main: Cory Booker Expects to Miss Next Debate but Won't Drop Out
headline_print_headline: Cory Booker Expects to Miss Next Debate but Won't Drop Out

abstract: Cory Booker will try to keep his presidential hopes alive by doubling down on the early voting state of Iowa, despite failing to qualify for next week's Democratic debate, his campaign said on Thursday.
snippet: Cory Booker will try to keep his presidential hopes alive by doubling down on the early voting state of Iowa, despite failing to qualify for next week's Democratic debate, his campaign said on Thursday.
lead_paragraph: LOS ANGELES — Cory Booker will try to keep his presidential hopes alive by doubling down on the early voting state of Iowa, despite failing to qualify for next week's Democratic debate, his campaign said on Thursday.
headline_main: Democrat Booker Doubling Down in Iowa After Failing to Make Debate
headline_print_headline: Democrat Booker Doubling Down in Iowa After Failing to Make Debate

abstract: - The U.S. House of Representatives on Thursday approved legislation aimed at driving down the prices that seniors pay for prescription drugs, but the bill's future is clouded by President Donald Trump's threat of a veto and lack of support in the Senate.
snippet: - The U.S. House of Representatives on Thursday approved legislation aimed at driving down the prices that seniors pay for prescription drugs, but the bill's future is clouded by President Donald Trump's threat of a veto and lack of support in the...
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — - The U.S. House of Representatives on Thursday approved legislation aimed at driving down the prices that seniors pay for prescription drugs, but the bill's future is clouded by President Donald Trump's threat of a veto and lack of support in the Senate.
headline_main: Democrats Pass U.S. Bill to Lower Drug Prices That Trump Threatens to Veto
headline_print_headline: Democrats Pass U.S. Bill to Lower Drug Prices That Trump Threatens to Veto

abstract: Twitter is bringing back special labels to help users identify accounts and tweets from U.S. political candidates.
snippet: Twitter is bringing back special labels to help users identify accounts and tweets from U.S. political candidates.
lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — Twitter is bringing back special labels to help users identify accounts and tweets from U.S. political candidates.
headline_main: Twitter Brings Back Election Labels for 2020 US Candidates
headline_print_headline: Twitter Brings Back Election Labels for 2020 US Candidates

abstract: Top Democrats and Republicans said they had an “agreement in principle” on $1.37 trillion in federal spending to keep the government funded through the end of the year.
snippet: Top Democrats and Republicans said they had an “agreement in principle” on $1.37 trillion in federal spending to keep the government funded through the end of the year.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Senior lawmakers announced on Thursday that they had reached a tentative bipartisan agreement on funding the government for the remainder of the fiscal year, offering a solution to avert a shutdown after weeks of haggling over money for President Trump’s border wall and other matters.

abstract: It's been true for some time that Republicans are generally more hostile to the news media than Democrats, but a study released Thursday found that's much more the case for supporters of President Donald Trump.
snippet: It's been true for some time that Republicans are generally more hostile to the news media than Democrats, but a study released Thursday found that's much more the case for supporters of President Donald Trump.
lead_paragraph: NEW YORK — It's been true for some time that Republicans are generally more hostile to the news media than Democrats, but a study released Thursday found that's much more the case for supporters of President Donald Trump.
headline_main: Study Shows Hostility Toward Journalists by Trump Fans
headline_print_headline: Study Shows Hostility Toward Journalists by Trump Fans

abstract: First the doctors attacked the lawyers. Then the lawyers attacked the doctors. Now the lawyers are under arrest, and three patients are dead.
snippet: First the doctors attacked the lawyers. Then the lawyers attacked the doctors. Now the lawyers are under arrest, and three patients are dead.
lead_paragraph: ISLAMABAD, Pakistan — Clad in black suits, white shirts and black ties, hundreds of lawyers forced their way into the Lahore cardiology hospital, smashing windows and damaging equipment. Doctors ran for cover, and unattended, panicked patients ran for their lives. The hospital wards were littered with shards of glass and broken furniture.
headline_main: In Pakistan Hospital, It Was Lawyers vs. Doctors. 3 Patients Died.
headline_print_headline: In Pakistan, A Brawl Pits Lawyers Vs. Doctors

abstract: The United States imposed sanctions on another son of Nicaraguan President Daniel Ortega, Rafael, on Thursday, accusing him of money laundering and corruption, in the latest effort by Washington to put pressure on the leftist government.
snippet: The United States imposed sanctions on another son of Nicaraguan President Daniel Ortega, Rafael, on Thursday, accusing him of money laundering and corruption, in the latest effort by Washington to put pressure on the leftist government.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The United States imposed sanctions on another son of Nicaraguan President Daniel Ortega, Rafael, on Thursday, accusing him of money laundering and corruption, in the latest effort by Washington to put pressure on the leftist government.
headline_main: U.S. Imposes Sanctions on Son of Nicaragua's President
headline_print_headline: U.S. Imposes Sanctions on Son of Nicaragua's President
